# Retrobox

## Install

- Format SDCard (FAT32)

- Download Retropie
- Mount retropie image on SDCard
- Insert SDCard into RPi
- Exit from Retropie - Press F4 when prompt and after press spacebar

- Type sudo raspi-config to open raspberry configudation
- Select **Expand File System**
- Type sudo reboot at prompt

## Language & Keyboard

- Press F4 to quit Retropie and Spacebar
- Type sudo raspi-config to open Raspberry configuration
- Select International options
  - Select Change Locale
    - Uncheck en_GB UTF8 **spacebar**
    - Check fr_FR ISO 8859-1 **spacebar**
    - Check fr_FR UTF8 **spacebar**
    - press **enter**
    - select fr_FR UTF8 as default **enter**
  - Select Change Timezone
    - Select Europe
    - Select Paris
  - Change Keyboard Layout
    - Select Generic 105 Key
    - Select Other
    - Select French
    - Select French
    - Select The Default for the keyboard input (top list option)
    - Select No Compose Key
    - Select No for X Server
    - Quit to prompt
    - Type sudo reboot at prompt
    
## Update Raspberry OS

- Press F4 to exit to prompt
- Type sudo apt-get update at prompt
- Type sudo apt-get upgrade at prompt

